House State & Local Government 1
Amendment No. 1 to HB2314
Crawford
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2481* House Bill No. 2314
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 7-51-1104, is amended by adding
the following as new subsections:
(g) The board shall not issue a license unless the applicant certifies that a sign
no smaller than eight and one-half inches by eleven inches (8 1/2" x 11") is posted at
each entrance of the establishment that states: "Attention: By engaging in this type of
entertainment, you may be contributing to an increase in domestic assault, rape or
sexual assault, and human trafficking.".
(h) If an adult-oriented establishment lawfully offers for sale, loan, or use
sexually oriented materials, including print, video, and other media, then the board shall
not issue a license to the establishment unless the applicant certifies that signs are
posted at each display of sexually oriented material that states: "For Your Information:
Production of these materials may contribute to an increase in domestic assault, rape or
sexual assault, and human trafficking.".
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
